    <div class="row">
      <h3>Pitch/Purpose</h3>
      <p>Nowadays configuring <a href="https://developers.google.com/analytics/devguides/collection/analyticsjs/sending-hits#the_send_method" target="_blank">custom events for Google Analytics</a> is a laborious job which involves making changes to code and deploys to production whenever any changes are required.
      In one sentence, Google Analytics sourcing made incredibly easy. Really.</p>

      <p>With No Fuss Analytics we allow anyone who wants to track these events not to touch code. No engineering; No deploys; No inflexibility; Save Engineering time and empower your Marketing, Product and UX teams.</p>

      <p>All you have to do is to embed a <code>&lt;script&gt;</code> tag on your site and start tracking clicks! You can even use existing click events or easily create new rules for existing elements on your page via an awesome bookmarklet.</p>

      <p>It focuses on the Productivity and a bit on Data Visualizations:</p>
      <ul>
      <li><span style="font-weight: bolder;font-size:1em;">Productivity</span>: as previously stated, by using No Fuss Analytics, companies can have an autonomous flow in what regards to acting in the most relevant way they can: driven by data. By separating the concern of coding the pipelines to send data from simply sending data, there's no need for changes in code besides including the initial script.</li>
      <li><span style="font-weight: bolder;;font-size:1em;">Data Visualizations</span>: while not providing Data Visualization per-se, it clearly allows to leverage the capabilities of Data Visualization of Google Analytics. We do render the elements that are clicked, which is amazing. Not sure it counts? :)</li>
      </ul>


